subSubSection.paragraph:
Ventral region: Structure normal for the genus, without specific characters. Epimeral setal formula 3-1-3-3; with transverse grooves (
'taenidium'
) between epimeres IV and ventral plate, as typical of family. Genital and anal plates large, only slightly separated; five pairs of fine genital setae, one pair of aggenital setae, two pairs of anal setae, three pairs of adanal setae.
